Section 8.9: Lab — Monitor and Manage Linux Processes
    Start a program named sleep 300 in the background.
    List all running processes for the current user.
    Identify the PID of a running process.
    Stop a running process using its PID.

Section 8.10: Summary
    In one sentence, explain the difference between:
    A job is a command launched from the shell that may run in the foreground or background, while 
    A process is the running instance of a program managed by the operating system.

